node.title: Police investigation launched after baby arrives at Starship with 'non-accidental' critical injuries
node.description: "No one has been arrested at this stage."
node.content: ["Police are investigating after a baby was taken to Starship Hospital with critical injuries thought to be \"non-accidental\".", "In a statement to Newshub, Detective Inspector Aaron Proctor of the Waitemata police says police were told on Wednesday night that a 10-month old boy had arrived at Starship with critical injuries.\u00a0", "\"Police have launched an investigation and are currently in the process of carrying out a scene examination at an address in Birkdale. The child remains in a critical condition in hospital.\"", "Proctor says police believe the child's injuries are \"non-accidental\" and are working to establish the circumstances surrounding this.", "\"No one has been arrested at this stage.\""]
